gomodel:SYNGO_2787  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: [Fig.4: \"NOS1AP and Scrib colocalize to synaptophysin-positive presynaptic specializations in axons.\"\n- \"Together with our results showing that Scrib associates with presynaptic proteins, these localization data suggest that NOS1AP localizes with Scrib to presynaptic specializations, where it may play a role in synaptic vesicle dynamics and active zone formation.\"]\n\nFig.5: \"NOS1AP and Scrib colocalize in dendrites\"\n- \"We cotransfected dissociated rat hippocampal neurons with constructs encoding YFP-NOS1AP, CFP-Scrib, and RFP-synaptophysin. We saw colocalization of all three markers, supporting the notion that NOS1AP and Scrib could play a role presynaptically (Fig. 4G-J, arrows). This analysis showed colocalization of YFP-NOS1AP and actin in spine heads (Fig. 5K-M, arrows), supporting the notion that NOS1AP is found in dendritic spines. Together, these data suggest that NOS1AP and Scrib proteins can localize postsynaptically in dendritic spines.\". Experimental description: - \"Hippocampal neurons were isolated from E18 rat embryos as previously reported (Krueger et al., 2003). \"\n- Overexpressed NOS1AP is of rat species: \"Supplemental Figure 2. Rat NOS1APc cDNA sequence\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2018-03-08" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2787" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

